# Habit Tracker System — Entity Relationship Model (ERD)

This document describes the database structure of the Habit Tracker system, including entities, attributes, and relationships.

---

## 1. Entities and Attributes

### **1.1 User**
| Field         | Type      | Description                     |
|---------------|-----------|---------------------------------|
| UserId        | int (PK)  | Unique identifier for the user |
| Name          | string    | User's full name               |
| Email         | string    | User's email address           |
| PasswordHash  | string    | Encrypted password             |
| CreatedAt     | DateTime  | Account creation date          |

---

### **1.2 Habit**
| Field         | Type      | Description                         |
|---------------|-----------|-------------------------------------|
| HabitId       | int (PK)  | Unique identifier for the habit     |
| UserId        | int (FK)  | Reference to User                   |
| CategoryId    | int (FK)  | Reference to Category               |
| Name          | string    | Habit name                          |
| Description   | string    | Habit description                   |
| Frequency     | string    | daily / weekly / monthly            |
| CreatedAt     | DateTime  | Creation date                       |
| IsActive      | bool      | Whether the habit is active         |

---

### **1.3 Category**
| Field         | Type      | Description                         |
|---------------|-----------|-------------------------------------|
| CategoryId    | int (PK)  | Unique identifier for the category  |
| Name          | string    | Category name                       |

---

### **1.4 HabitCompletion**
| Field         | Type      | Description                         |
|---------------|-----------|-------------------------------------|
| CompletionId  | int (PK)  | Unique identifier for completion    |
| HabitId       | int (FK)  | Reference to Habit                  |
| CompletionDate| DateTime  | Date the habit was completed        |

---

## 2. Relationships

- **User 1 → N Habit**  
  A user can have multiple habits.

- **Category 1 → N Habit**  
  A category can group multiple habits.

- **Habit 1 → N HabitCompletion**  
  A habit can have multiple completion records.

---

